==English==

===Etymology===
From Middle English ''[[sithe]]'', from Old English ''[[siththa]]'' both of which literally mean: "shadowed face" or "a face hidden in the shadows."  Hence, the connotation is one of secrecy and concealment.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/sɪθ/

